The Anti-corruption law requires that the public officials should submit the below-listed information;  
-their annual income, indicating the source, type and amount;
-property that is the object of taxation;
-deposits, securities and other financial resources in credit organizations;
-participation in the activities of companies, funds and other economic entities as a shareholder or founder, his share of ownership in these enterprises;
- the debt exceeding five thousand five hundred manats; 
-other financial and property obligations over one thousand one hundred manats. (Article 5) (13.01.2004 № 580-IIQ) (2) 
The law "On approval of the Rules for submission of financial information by officials" stipulates that some officials should submit their declaration to the Anti-Corruption Commission of the Republic of Azerbaijan (relating to the officials mentioned in article 3.1). Parliament and other organizations define relevant agencies themselves. But the law as mentioned above does not include any requirement related to disclosure of required data. The law defines such content as confidential information. (Article 9.1 and 9.2) (24/06/ 2005 № 945-IIQ)(1)

Conclusion
Although the law provides for the submission of such information, it is not required to be open or justified. As it is confidential, the receiving public agencies should protect them and it cannot be shared publicly. 

